18:42.440 --> 18:43.840
Oh, like a... Like a chauffeur.

18:43.920 --> 18:45.513
You drive around important people?

18:45.600 --> 18:46.875
I guess I do.

18:46.960 --> 18:48.314
Anyone I'd know?

18:48.400 --> 18:49.629
I hope not.

18:49.720 --> 18:51.279
Well, aren't you mysterious.

18:51.880 --> 18:52.836
Maybe.

18:52.920 --> 18:54.673
(LAUGHS) Maybe?

18:56.080 --> 18:58.470
So, when was the last time
you hit the road just for fun?

18:58.560 --> 18:59.960
Yesterday.

19:00.040 --> 19:01.474
Oh, then I'm jealous.

19:01.560 --> 19:04.120
Sometimes all I want to do
is head west on 20

19:04.200 --> 19:06.431
in a car I can't afford
with a plan I don't have.

19:07.320 --> 19:10.074
Just me, my music and the road.

19:10.160 --> 19:11.310
I'd like that, too.

19:11.400 --> 19:12.800
(COOK CLEARS THROAT LOUDLY)

19:12.920 --> 19:13.956
(CLEARS THROAT) Oh.

19:14.040 --> 19:15.679
Uh, so, you decide on anything yet?

19:15.800 --> 19:18.315
You are so beautiful.

19:18.560 --> 19:20.552
(LAUGHS) You just decided that.

19:20.680 --> 19:22.399
Oh, well, thank you.

19:23.240 --> 19:24.469
I'm sure you don't mean it.

19:24.600 --> 19:25.920
I do mean it.

19:26.400 --> 19:27.436
Jonathan?

19:28.200 --> 19:29.236
Oh, sorry.

19:29.880 --> 19:31.075
You know, this isn't my badge.

19:31.160 --> 19:33.470
- I've only just started here, so...
- As a Jonathan?

19:34.280 --> 19:36.351
Yeah. (LAUGHS) As a Jonathan.

19:37.320 --> 19:39.710
Well, um, if you have any more questions,
just holler.

19:41.320 --> 19:45.280
B-A-B-Y, baby

19:45.360 --> 19:46.430
I have a question.

19:47.760 --> 19:49.114
What's that song you're singing?

19:51.080 --> 19:53.072
(B-A-B-Y BY CARLA THOMAS PLAYING)

19:59.280 --> 20:02.910
- (MOUTHING TO RECORD)
- WOMAN: (SINGING) Baby, oh, baby

20:03.520 --> 20:06.638
I love to call you baby

20:07.680 --> 20:11.196
Baby, oh, baby

20:11.280 --> 20:15.513
I love for you to call me baby

20:15.600 --> 20:19.150
When you squeeze me real tight...

20:19.280 --> 20:20.430
I approve.

20:20.520 --> 20:21.920
Of the song?

20:22.000 --> 20:24.151
Of the girl.

20:25.280 --> 20:28.796
And I can't stop loving you

20:29.280 --> 20:32.717
And I won't stop calling you

20:33.160 --> 20:34.116
(BUZZING)

20:34.200 --> 20:36.317
Baby, oh, baby

20:36.880 --> 20:40.396
You look so good to me, baby

20:42.720 --> 20:45.360
DOC: Oh, there you are.
I've been calling, Baby.

20:45.440 --> 20:46.999
- You have?
- I have.

20:47.080 --> 20:49.390
My chicken just laid a very big egg.

20:49.480 --> 20:51.437
- You in?
- Am I in?

20:51.560 --> 20:53.597
It was a rhetorical question, Baby.

20:54.320 --> 20:55.754
You're in.

20:55.840 --> 20:57.160
I'll be there.

20:58.000 --> 21:00.834
(KASHMERE BY
THE KASHMERE STAGE BAND PLAYS)

21:07.760 --> 21:09.399
Meet your new crew.

21:09.480 --> 21:12.917
Over here is Eddie No Nose,
formerly Eddie The Nose.

21:13.040 --> 21:14.110
Why, what happened?

21:14.200 --> 21:15.600
Don't ask me that.

21:15.680 --> 21:17.751
That's a No Nose no-no, page one.

21:17.880 --> 21:19.030
And right here is JD.

21:19.120 --> 21:21.032
He put the "Asian" in home invasion.

21:21.120 --> 21:23.191
And over there is the one and the only Bats.

21:23.280 --> 21:24.600
No need for intros, Doc.

21:24.720 --> 21:27.394
Everybody from the jungle
to the trap know Bats.

21:30.040 --> 21:31.269
This your boy, right?

21:31.360 --> 21:33.636
This the one you say
listens to the music all the time?

21:34.640 --> 21:37.030
The driver's supposed
to be the eyes and the ears,

21:37.880 --> 21:39.109
not just the eyes.

21:39.200 --> 21:41.715
Why does he listen to music
all the time, Doc?

21:41.800 --> 21:43.473
- He's got mental problems?
- BATS: No, no, no, no.

21:43.560 --> 21:46.314
I'm the one got the mental problems
in the crew.

21:46.400 --> 21:48.756
- Position taken.
- DOC: He's got tinnitus.

21:48.840 --> 21:51.639
- Tinna-what?
- He had an accident when he was a kid.

21:51.720 --> 21:54.360
He's still got a hum in the drum.
Plays music to drown it out.

21:55.680 --> 21:56.955
(HIGH-PITCHED RINGING IN EARS)

21:57.040 --> 21:58.633
Yeah, but you feel me.

22:02.360 --> 22:03.350
BABY: Hat?

22:03.520 --> 22:04.476
Huh?

22:04.560 --> 22:05.789
Your tattoo says, "Hat."

22:06.240 --> 22:08.709
Yeah. It used to say "Hate."

22:08.800 --> 22:11.838
But to increase my chances of employment,
I got the "E" removed.

22:12.440 --> 22:13.874
How's that working out for you?

22:13.960 --> 22:15.758
Who doesn't like hats?

22:16.240 --> 22:17.310
BATS: So, Doc,

22:17.440 --> 22:19.113
how many jobs you done with the kid?

22:19.240 --> 22:22.438
If you can't take my word for him,
then get back in that fucking elevator.

22:23.440 --> 22:25.636
You never heard of the Spirit of 85?

22:27.360 --> 22:28.999
- The joyrider?
- Yeah.

22:29.080 --> 22:32.357
The ghost that baited cops doing 130 on 85.

22:32.440 --> 22:34.671
Headlights off, brake lights disconnected.

22:34.760 --> 22:37.150
He drove 'em around in circles
on Spaghetti Junction.

22:37.240 --> 22:39.835
Left 'em in the dust every time.
That was our boy there.

22:39.960 --> 22:41.076
- Wasn't that, like, 10 years ago?
- Yeah.

22:41.160 --> 22:42.674
Well, like I said, that was our boy.

22:42.760 --> 22:44.274
He's been boosting cars
since he was old enough

22:44.360 --> 22:45.396
to see over the dash.

22:45.480 --> 22:47.597
He stole my Mercedes.
Had a lot of merch in it.

22:47.720 --> 22:49.518
I watched him do it, too.
I didn't stop him, though,

22:49.600 --> 22:51.990
'cause I was just blinded
by the balls on that kid.

22:52.080 --> 22:53.673
'Course he didn't know who I was,

22:53.760 --> 22:56.036
or the worth of the junk in the trunk
once he dumped it,

22:56.120 --> 22:59.192
but once I tracked him down,
I made sure to tell him who I was,

22:59.280 --> 23:02.034
what I was capable of,
and how much he owed me.

23:02.120 --> 23:05.431
And since he's been paying me back,
he's also shown me what he's capable of.

23:05.520 --> 23:06.556
Wow.

23:06.640 --> 23:10.031
I just drew a whole goddamn map in chalk
while we've been standing here squawking.

23:10.120 --> 23:12.237
That's pretty fucking impressive, right?

23:13.160 --> 23:16.153
Shop, let's talk it. Baby, you with us?

23:16.240 --> 23:18.152
(UNSQUARE DANCE BY
THE DAVE BRUBECK QUARTET PLAYING)

23:20.720 --> 23:21.790
(INAUDIBLE)

23:27.520 --> 23:29.989
(JAZZ PIANO PLAYING,
RHYTHMIC CLAPPING)

23:38.160 --> 23:39.480
