- You're back.
- (BABY SIGHS)

35:34.080 --> 35:36.072
- I sure am.
- Well, then, you, sir,

35:36.160 --> 35:37.879
are gonna be my very last customer,

35:37.960 --> 35:41.032
because I am walking out that door
in precisely 30 seconds.

35:41.120 --> 35:43.510
- You're leaving?
- Yes, sir.

35:43.600 --> 35:44.636
Can I come with you?

35:44.720 --> 35:46.393
(CHUCKLES)
You don't have work or nothing?

35:48.400 --> 35:51.632
Uh, I don't. I am done with work.

35:51.720 --> 35:52.949
Wow. You seem real happy about that.

35:53.040 --> 35:54.554
- Yeah, I sure am.
- (POTS CLATTERING)

35:54.640 --> 35:55.676
COOK: God damn it!

35:55.760 --> 35:58.400
I don't blame you.
Well, you're welcome to come with,

35:58.480 --> 36:00.995
but I don't know how exciting
you're gonna find the laundromat.

36:01.160 --> 36:02.150
Huh?

36:02.240 --> 36:04.277
- I got to run some errands.
- Oh.

36:04.560 --> 36:07.997
But think about what you want,
and I will stick around just for you.

36:08.080 --> 36:09.116
Coffee?

36:09.200 --> 36:11.396
Please. Uh, cream and sugar.

36:12.440 --> 36:14.875
So, how you two getting along?

36:14.960 --> 36:15.996
Oh, good.

36:16.080 --> 36:17.719
He's sweet, isn't he?

36:17.800 --> 36:20.520
That kid?
He's been coming here since before me.

36:20.600 --> 36:22.796
Think maybe his mom used to work here.

36:23.760 --> 36:24.796
Huh.

36:27.720 --> 36:28.790
Know what you want?

36:28.880 --> 36:30.758
(MUFFLED MUSIC PLAYING OVER EARBUDS)

36:31.560 --> 36:32.596
Your name?

36:32.960 --> 36:34.917
Well, you can get that for free.

36:35.200 --> 36:37.510
- (RECORDER CLICKS ON)
- It's Debbie. Debora.

36:37.600 --> 36:39.512
- (RECORDER CLICKS OFF)
- Oh, like the song.

36:39.600 --> 36:41.432
The Beck one? Yeah.

36:41.520 --> 36:45.196
Well, except I'm D-E-B-O-R-A,
and I think that's just D-E-B-R-A.

36:45.280 --> 36:46.475
I don't know that one.

36:46.880 --> 36:47.950
Oh, it goes, um...

36:48.320 --> 36:49.436
(CLEARS THROAT)

36:51.960 --> 36:54.998
(SINGING SOFTLY) I met you at JCPenney

36:55.080 --> 36:56.116
(CLEARS THROAT)

36:57.280 --> 37:00.318
I think your nametag said Jenny

37:00.640 --> 37:01.835
Jenny?

37:02.040 --> 37:04.236
The song's about him wanting
to get with Jenny

37:04.320 --> 37:06.755
and her sister, too, whose name is Debra.

37:06.960 --> 37:09.873
So it's not even really about me.
It's about the sister.

37:10.640 --> 37:14.429
My sister's name is Mary.
She has got all the songs.

37:14.520 --> 37:16.113
"Mary, Mary, where you goin' to?"

37:16.200 --> 37:17.998
"Proud Mary keep on burnin'."

37:18.080 --> 37:19.400
"The Wind Cries Mary."

37:19.720 --> 37:21.677
She's got me beat. Again.

37:22.120 --> 37:24.919
She's got endless songs. I got one.

37:25.320 --> 37:26.470
No, you got two.

37:27.160 --> 37:28.310
What's the other one?

37:28.400 --> 37:29.914
Debora, the song I'm talking about.

37:30.000 --> 37:31.639
- (LAUGHS) Who by?
- Trex.

37:32.720 --> 37:33.756
T.Rex?

37:34.000 --> 37:35.320
Uh, yeah.

37:35.440 --> 37:37.033
(CHUCKLES) I've heard of them,
but don't know that one.

37:37.120 --> 37:38.349
How's it go?

37:39.840 --> 37:41.433
- (RECORDER CLICKS ON)
- Oh. (LAUGHS)

37:41.840 --> 37:44.230
(SINGING) Oh, oh, Debora

37:44.320 --> 37:46.789
Always look like a zeb-ora

37:46.880 --> 37:48.280
"A zeb-ora"?

37:48.360 --> 37:49.714
- Like a zebra, I guess.
- (LAUGHS)

37:49.800 --> 37:51.439
- Yeah.
- Well, I'm wearing black and white,

37:51.520 --> 37:53.079
so you can call me Deebra.

37:53.160 --> 37:54.230
(BOTH LAUGHING)

37:54.320 --> 37:56.596
Actually, I actually got Debora on here.

37:56.680 --> 37:59.240
Okay, what?
How many of those do you have?

38:00.120 --> 38:03.238
Oh, I got different iPods
for different days and moods.

38:03.880 --> 38:06.349
Oh. And you're in a pink and glittery mood.

38:07.320 --> 38:08.959
I am now.

38:09.040 --> 38:10.030
(DEBORA GIGGLES)

38:11.200 --> 38:12.475
What is your name?

38:12.600 --> 38:14.353
- Baby.
- Wait, what?

38:14.720 --> 38:15.915
Your name's Baby?

38:16.040 --> 38:17.554
B-A-B-Y, Baby?

38:17.720 --> 38:18.870
Yeah.

38:19.000 --> 38:20.719
Well, then, you have us all beat.

38:20.960 --> 38:23.156
- (CHUCKLES)
- Every damn song is about you.

38:23.640 --> 38:25.916
We could drive back and forth
across the States forever

38:26.000 --> 38:27.832
and never run out of "Baby" songs.

38:27.920 --> 38:29.752
We might run out of gas, though.

38:29.840 --> 38:30.876
(DEBORA LAUGHS)

38:31.560 --> 38:34.632
Did your mom call you "Baby" as a kid?

38:35.320 --> 38:36.356
Sometimes.

38:36.440 --> 38:38.238
She used to work here?

38:39.240 --> 38:42.631
Sometimes, but, uh, she was a singer, too.

38:43.560 --> 38:45.233
What does she do now?

38:47.000 --> 38:48.116
Nothing.

38:50.000 --> 38:52.071
Uh, I could find Debora if you want.

38:52.320 --> 38:53.390
COOK: Debbie!

38:54.240 --> 38:55.754
(SIGHS) For crying out loud.

38:57.160 --> 39:00.437
Well, uh, play it for me sometime
I don't have to get out of here.

39:01.080 --> 39:03.231
- Deal?
- Yeah, deal.

39:04.120 --> 39:05.918
Now, you know what you want yet?

39:06.480 --> 39:07.834
To get out of here.

39:08.480 --> 39:10.756
- (DEBORA BY T.REX PLAYS)
- (DOOR BELL CHIMES)

39:11.240 --> 39:13.914
MAN: (SINGING) Dug-a-re-dug,
dug-a-re-dug-a-da

39:14.000 --> 39:19.439
Dug-a-re-dug, dug-a-re-dug-a-da

39:19.520 --> 39:21.591
Dug-a-re-dug, dug-a-re-dug

39:21.680 --> 39:25.799
Oh, Debora, always look like a zeb-ora

39:25.880 --> 39:27.917
- (LAUGHS)
- Your sunken face...

39:28.000 --> 39:31.152
You're right. I do like it.

39:31.240 --> 39:32.879
Good.

39:32.960 --> 39:35.714
So, what's your story, Baby?

39:35.800 --> 39:37.200
You from here?

39:37.280 --> 39:38.760
I am.

39:38.840 --> 39:40.957
Keep going. Keep going.

39:41.640 --> 39:43.313
- You're from here.
- Uh-huh.

39:43.440 --> 39:47.116
You're a driver. You like music.
You don't talk much.

39:47.640 --> 39:48.710
No.

39:48.800 --> 39:52.237
I've, uh, spoken more to you today

39:52.320 --> 39:55.438
- than I have to anyone all year.
- Whoa.

39:55.520 --> 39:57.273
Okay.

39:57.360 --> 39:59.795
Not a motor-mouth. Noted.

39:59.880 --> 40:01.473
Yeah, yeah. I have...

40:02.080 --> 40:04.117
I have this, uh, hearing thing.

40:05.200 --> 40:06.873
I was in an accident when I was little.

40:07.440 --> 40:08.840
Is that what happened to your mom?

40:08.920 --> 40:10.479
Yeah. Yeah, and my dad.

40:11.960 --> 40:12.996
I miss her.

40:14.960 --> 40:17.111
- I'm sorry.
- No, don't be.

40:17.240 --> 40:19.835
I live with my foster dad,
but now he's getting old,

40:19.920 --> 40:22.116
so it's more like I'm looking after him.

40:22.240 --> 40:24.311
Yeah. I know how that feels.

40:25.440 --> 40:28.035
I had to look after my mom
when she got sick.

40:28.520 --> 40:31.319
It might seem tough now,
but once they're gone,

40:31.400 --> 40:33.471
you'll miss having someone to care for.

40:35.000 --> 40:37.595
I don't have much to keep me here anymore.

40:38.400 --> 40:39.390
You don't?

40:40.200 --> 40:41.839
(DOOR BELL CHIMES)

40:43.520 --> 40:44.920
You know,

40:45.520 --> 40:49.434
mmm, we could get together
some other time, some other place?

40:50.000 --> 40:53.914
Oh, you mean, uh, somewhere
that's not a diner or a laundromat?

40:54.000 --> 40:56.799
(GIGGLES) Yeah, well,
it's not that this isn't nice but...

40:56.880 --> 41:00.396
Oh, well, we could go to, uh... Um...

41:01.080 --> 41:02.196
Oh, Bacchanalia.

41:02.600 --> 41:04.557
I've never been. I... I hear it's nice.

41:04.880 --> 41:09.159
Oh, it's... It's the finest winin' and dinin'
of all the wines and dines in town.

41:09.360 --> 41:10.874
(CHUCKLES) That is nice.

41:12.080 --> 41:13.992
Um, but they got me pulling doubles
this week, though.

41:14.240 --> 41:16.232
What about next week?
What's your schedule like?

41:16.400 --> 41:17.436
I don't know.

41:17.520 --> 41:20.240
Oh, I forgot. They call, you go.

41:20.320 --> 41:22.198
No, I mean, I'm... I'm not working.

41:22.280 --> 41:24.636
- You're not driving anymore?
- No.

41:25.000 --> 41:26.400
I'm sorry.

41:26.560 --> 41:28.074
No, don't be. It's my choice.

41:28.560 --> 41:30.870
Well, aren't you the lucky one.

41:31.000 --> 41:34.072
MAN: (SINGING) I want to get with you

41:34.200 --> 41:37.238
Only you, girl

41:37.560 --> 41:40.598
And your sister

41:40.720 --> 41:42.791
- (MOUTHING)
- I think her name's Debra

41:42.880 --> 41:44.792
Oh, oh...

41:47.200 --> 41:49.590
So who's Debora?

41:50.240 --> 41:52.118
The girl.

41:52.200 --> 41:53.190
(SIGHS)

41:53.320 --> 41:55.596
NEWSCASTER: (ON TV)
His name, Malik Kelly, a local veteran.

41:56.600 --> 42:00.435
You saw what these folks were doing.
You took action. Why?

42:00.520 --> 42:01.874
I'm done.

42:01.960 --> 42:04.839
MALIK: I saw these guys go
marching in the bank with Halloween masks,

42:04.920 --> 42:06.195
weapons drawn.

42:06.280 --> 42:07.396
They were attacking...

42:07.480 --> 42:08.596
Is this the place?

42:10.080 --> 42:11.514
##

42:12.800 --> 42:14.234
Here.

42:15.800 --> 42:16.790
Pizza?

42:16.880 --> 42:19.156
Are we celebrating?

42:19.880 --> 42:21.394
Celebrating you getting

42:21.480 --> 42:23.073
a real job.

42:24.600 --> 42:26.000
What kind of job?

42:26.360 --> 42:27.430
Wouldn't it be good

42:27.520 --> 42:30.911
to bring joy to people

42:31.000 --> 42:34.311
when you drive?

42:35.280 --> 42:36.600
Pizza?

42:37.120 --> 42:38.634
##

42:40.720 --> 42:41.836
(BELL CHIMES)

42:41.920 --> 42:43.354
MAN: Order's up!

42:53.560 --> 42:54.550
(ENGINE STARTS)

42:54.800 --> 42:55.916
(TIRES SCREECHING)

43:01.360 --> 43:03.238
- (BUZZING)
- Whoa.

43:04.400 --> 43:05.390
That was fast.

43:05.760 --> 43:06.750
I know.

43:07.040 --> 43:09.111
- FRAT BOY: Pizza!
- (PEOPLE WHOOPING)

43:19.080 --> 43:20.594
Look...

43:21.200 --> 43:23.271
You only have to
wash your hands once

43:23.360 --> 43:24.999
after counting that.

43:25.680 --> 43:26.750
I know.

43:27.200 --> 43:28.520
And not put

43:28.600 --> 43:30.319
other lives

43:30.400 --> 43:31.390
in danger.

43:31.840 --> 43:35.356
I won't let anything bad
happen to you.

43:36.360 --> 43:37.794
I'm not talking

43:37.880 --> 43:39.234
about me.

43:39.560 --> 43:41.153
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

43:41.240 --> 43:42.515
(HORN HONKING)

43:43.160 --> 43:44.150
(ENGINE IDLING)

43:45.160 --> 43:46.310
##

43:50.240 --> 43:52.038
MAN: (SINGING) Baby, let me take you

43:55.440 --> 43:57.875
Let me take you in my arms

44:00.760 --> 44:03.958
Let me take you in my arms and hold you

44:07.720 --> 44:09.757
Show you I love you

44:10.800 --> 44:12.712
Baby, I love you

44:13.640 --> 44:15.552
Baby, I love you

44:16.240 --> 44:18.197
Baby, baby, I love you

44:18.520 --> 44:21.080
Don't love nobody else

44:21.160 --> 44:22.753
You got my love just for yourself...

44:22.840 --> 44:25.230
You're all good.
A gentleman picked this up already.

44:25.400 --> 44:26.390
A gentleman?

44:28.000 --> 44:29.753
Who is that?

44:30.920 --> 44:32.593
BABY: It's my old boss.

44:33.880 --> 44:34.870
Uh...

44:35.600 --> 44:37.239
Excuse me one second.

44:39.160 --> 44:40.913
VALET: Here you are, madam.
WOMAN: Thank you very much.

44:41.880 --> 44:43.109
VALET: Have a good night.

44:45.880 --> 44:47.200
Good meal, Baby?

44:47.280 --> 44:49.511
That foie gras terrine is something, huh?

44:50.120 --> 44:51.110
Yeah.

44:51.440 --> 44:53.193
You don't look happy to see me. Why?

44:53.320 --> 44:55.630
I said we were straight,
but did you think we were done?

44:56.000 --> 44:57.275
That that was it?

44:57.680 --> 44:59.797
Uh, I guess I did.

44:59.880 --> 45:02.395
Well, I could give you
the good news and the bad news,

45:02.480 --> 45:04.312
except there is no bad news.

45:04.400 --> 45:06.790
The good news is
you're about to make a lot of money.

45:06.960 --> 45:10.271
And the good news is
you're about to make a lot of money.

45:10.440 --> 45:12.033
I got... I got a job, Doc.

45:12.120 --> 45:14.919
Yeah, but why slave away
delivering GoodFellas pizzas

45:15.000 --> 45:17.196
just to afford a night out here,

45:17.280 --> 45:20.432
when you could make all that dough
with a great fella? Me.

45:20.520 --> 45:23.957
And then take your gal here
for fucking dinner every night of the week?

45:24.120 --> 45:26.715
You paid off your debt.
Now it's time to profit.

45:26.800 --> 45:28.393
This is the fun bit, Baby.

45:28.480 --> 45:30.711
By the time this job is over,
you'll be rolling in money,

45:30.800 --> 45:35.431
buying Maseratis and feeding your gal
catfish dipped in gold.

45:35.520 --> 45:36.715
So, what do you say? You in?

45:38.240 --> 45:39.594
Am I in?

45:39.720 --> 45:41.791
No, don't answer my question
with another question.

45:41.880 --> 45:44.315
You give me one of two replies. Yes or no.

45:46.160 --> 45:47.389
No, Doc.

45:49.040 --> 45:51.999
You know I never do a job
with the exact same crew twice, right?

45:52.680 --> 45:54.080
- Yes.
- And you also know

45:54.160 --> 45:56.550
you've been my driver
for every job since we met.

45:57.480 --> 45:58.800
Yes.

46:00.400 --> 46:04.235
So, I'm of the thinking
that you are my lucky charm

46:04.320 --> 46:07.040
and that I'm not doing this job without you.

46:08.000 --> 46:09.400
Now, I don't think
I need to give you the speech

46:09.480 --> 46:10.880
about what happens when you say no,

46:10.960 --> 46:12.792
how I could break your legs
and kill everyone you love,

46:12.880 --> 46:14.519
because you already know that, don't you?

46:16.080 --> 46:17.196
Yeah.

46:17.760 --> 46:19.274
So, what's it gonna be,

46:19.360 --> 46:21.352
behind the wheel or in a wheelchair?

46:22.200 --> 46:23.350
The first one.

46:25.800 --> 46:27.029
I'll pick you up in the morning.

46:28.200 --> 46:29.919
Don't stay out too late, now.

46:30.080 --> 46:31.070
Oh.

46:31.160 --> 46:34.597
And your, uh, waitress girlfriend,
she's cute.

46:35.160 --> 46:36.913
Let's keep it that way.

46:37.360 --> 46:39.158
VALET: Good night, sir.

46:43.000 --> 46:46.311
DEBORA: Well, that was some pretty fine
winin' and dinin'.

46:46.880 --> 46:49.759
Must have friends in high places
to get a table there.

46:50.160 --> 46:51.879
BABY: Oh, I don't know about that.

46:54.400 --> 46:56.392
Is everything okay, Baby?

46:59.760 --> 47:01.479
It will be.

47:01.560 --> 47:04.951
You want to talk about it?
I make a mean cup of coffee.

47:05.520 --> 47:08.911
I mean, I... I don't. I make terrible coffee.

47:09.600 --> 47:11.512
I want to, but I...

47:11.960 --> 47:13.474
I can't right now.

47:13.600 --> 47:15.353
You know, you...

47:16.080 --> 47:18.311
You don't have to worry about me.

47:19.080 --> 47:20.560
You can tell me anything.

47:20.640 --> 47:21.994
I'm not worried about you.

47:22.080 --> 47:23.594
I mean, I...

47:24.840 --> 47:27.674
You're the best thing
that's happened to me in a long time.

47:28.920 --> 47:34.279
And I just worry that
I'm not good enough for you.

47:35.280 --> 47:38.079
Oh, well, don't.

47:40.600 --> 47:44.674
I can see you're kind and you're different.

47:46.520 --> 47:48.989
And I'm here for you when you're ready.

48:01.360 --> 48:02.680
What are you doing tomorrow?

48:05.360 --> 48:06.794
Uh, you tell me.

48:11.760 --> 48:13.240
(EARS RINGING)

48:14.280 --> 48:15.430
(SIGHS)

48:17.280 --> 48:18.873
##

48:23.720 --> 48:24.995
(HORN HONKS)

48:29.840 --> 48:31.479
Good morning.

48:33.920 --> 48:36.116
These places never get rolled.

48:36.200 --> 48:38.920
People don't realize
that there's gold in them there hills.

48:39.000 --> 48:43.199
And those that do, don't have the stones
to pull off a job so public in the hub of it.

48:43.280 --> 48:45.078
This place'll be ripe
around this time tomorrow,

48:45.160 --> 48:46.719
but I need you to do something for me today.

48:47.320 --> 48:49.357
I can't be seen in there, but you can.

48:49.440 --> 48:50.430
So go inside.

48:50.680 --> 48:53.195
Take note of the number
of cameras and positions,

48:53.360 --> 48:54.999
the number of registers open,

48:55.200 --> 48:57.476
the number of employees
and the number of customers.

48:57.680 --> 48:59.353
Is there a guard? Is he armed?

48:59.480 --> 49:00.834
Do they have bandit glass?

49:01.520 --> 49:03.591
And get in line, buy some stamps.

49:03.680 --> 49:06.354
Take your buds out, pull your shades off.

49:07.200 --> 49:10.432
Oh, and, uh, take the nephew.
Less suspicious.

49:11.520 --> 49:12.590
(SIGHS)

49:12.720 --> 49:13.710
(DOOR CHIMES)

49:14.400 --> 49:16.198
RECORDED VOICE: (OVER PA)
The United States Postal Service.

49:16.360 --> 49:19.592
We're here, working for you,
seven days a week.

49:19.720 --> 49:22.360
We do a lot more
than just stamps these days.

49:22.560 --> 49:25.029
You'd be surprised at what we have to offer.

49:25.960 --> 49:28.031
MAN: (OVER RADIO)
Yeah, Jack, all looks fine back here. Over.

49:28.120 --> 49:29.440
(EARS RINGING)

49:40.200 --> 49:41.190
(BOY CLEARS THROAT)

49:43.560 --> 49:46.155
(WHISPERS) No bandit glass,
one armed guard,

49:46.240 --> 49:49.472
10 cameras, eight registers, two open,

49:49.560 --> 49:52.280
11 customers and four employees.

49:53.240 --> 49:54.560
- Thank you.
- (BELL CHIMES)

49:57.960 --> 49:58.950
Uh...

49:59.480 --> 50:00.914
Uh, stamps.

50:02.760 --> 50:04.114
That your boy?

50:04.760 --> 50:06.080
Sure.

50:06.440 --> 50:07.590
Yeah, he sure is.

50:07.680 --> 50:08.670
How old is he?

50:10.400 --> 50:12.073
- Four.
- Eight.

50:12.680 --> 50:14.990
They grow up so freaking fast, don't they?

50:15.080 --> 50:16.355
(LAUGHS)

50:17.360 --> 50:18.510
Does he have a name?

50:19.920 --> 50:21.149
You have a name, don't you?

50:21.440 --> 50:22.590
Samm.

50:22.680 --> 50:25.434
Well, Samm, I got a mint
with your name on it.

50:25.640 --> 50:28.235
You have a mint that says "Samm"?

50:28.320 --> 50:29.310
Aw.

50:29.720 --> 50:30.836
Sweet. (CHUCKLES)

50:31.640 --> 50:32.915
Are you here tomorrow?

50:33.000 --> 50:35.515
Sure am. Working 9:00 to 5:00,
just like Dolly.

50:36.600 --> 50:39.274
Oh, Dolly Parton. Yeah.

50:39.520 --> 50:41.591
- I like her.
- Mmm, who doesn't?

